data.text:
DELL — Barbara M., age 67, of Stuart Florida and Chatham, MA, beloved wife of 46 years of Glen A. Dell, died on Monday, August 23, 2004. Born in East Orange, New Jersey on January 21, 1937, she was a daughter of John N. and Eleanor W. Wilder Martin. She was a member of the Stuart, Florida Congregational Church and formerly a long term member of the Presbyterian Church of Old Greenwich, Connecticut where she also served as a family counselor. She was a graduate of Mount Holyoke College and earned a master degree from the University of Bridgeport. She was the great-granddaughter of H. Fisher Eldredge of Chatham. In addition to her husband, she is also survived by two children, Roger Dell and his wife, Betsy of Roseville, CA, and Karen Stratton and her husband, Bill of Trumbull, CT a sister Nancy Phelps of Chatham, MA godson Michael Chambers and six grandchildren. A memorial service will be held on Friday, August 27, 2004 at 11 am at the Stanwich Congregational Church, 237 Taconic Road, Greenwich, CT. Those desiring may make memorial contributions to the Eldredge Public Library in Chatham, the Stuart Congregational Church (Building Fund) 3110 SE Astor Lane, Stuart, Florida, 34994, or the National Cancer Society, Attention: WEB PO Box 102454, Atlanta, Georgia 30368.

DOHERTY - Hugh J. "Chip", of Hyannis, August 12. Husband of Sandra A. Doherty (Fedrini) father of Brian Hugh Doherty of Sagamore Beach, Phil A Doherty of Hyannis and James F. Doherty of Hyannis son of Edith Doherty (Reid) of Taunton brother of Eleanor Doherty of Taunton. A Funeral Mass will be celebrated in Saint Francis Xavier Church, South Street, Hyannis, on Friday, August 27, at 10 AM. Visiting Hours are omitted. Burial will be private. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to Hospice Palliative Care of Cape Cod, 270 Communication Way, Hyannis, MA 02601. Arrangements by John-Lawrence Funeral Home, Marstons Mills.

EMPLIT - Patricia J. "MaMa" (Eaton), of West Hyannisport, MA, passed away August 11, 2004, at Cape Cod Hospital at the age of 70. Born, raised and educated here on the Cape, Mrs. Emplit worked for many years in food service, and was known as "MaMa" by everyone. She loved to play cribbage, golf, and was an avid Red Sox fan. She loved her family, friends, and especially her grandchildren. She is survived by her husband Leon Emplit, they were married for 52 loving years. There are three daughters: Linda A. Poore of Sagamore, MA, Debora L. Kunze of Ohio, and Patricia A. Crocker of Marstons Mills, MA and two sons: Leon H. Emplit of Sandwich, MA, and Ernest H. Emplit of Hyannis, MA one sister Joan Birch also of Hyannis. There are eight grandchildren and one great-grandchild, also numerous nieces and nephews. A Celebration of Life Mass will be held August 28, 2004, at 10:00 AM at Our Lady of Victory, in Centerville, MA. Burial is private. In lieu of flowers, donations may be made to Multiple Sclerosis Society of MA, 101 First Ave.

6, Waltham, MA 02154-1115.

FITZGERALD - David C. in Needham, formerly of Belmont, August 20, age 55, after a lenghty illness. Graduate of Belmont High School. Served as a reservist in the Air Force National Guard, worked in retail sales and the mortgage industry, formerly Co-owned and operated a picture framing business with his former wife and friend Louisa Fitzgerald of Marshfield, son of the late Henry C. and Anna (Egan) Fitzgerald of Belmont and South Yarmouth. He also leaves his sisters Jeanne Mooney of Dedham, Anita Murphy of Marshfield brothers Paul Fitzgerald and Thomas Fitzgerald of Reading. From a previous marriage he leaves a daughter Keron Incarnato of New Haven, CT and many nieces and nephews. Service and Interment Private. Contributuions in David's memory to the American Cancer Society, 30 Speen Street, Framingham, MA 01701 or to the Stanley Tippett House, 920 South Street, Needham, MA 02492. Stanton Funeral Service 877-924-3838, www.stantonfuneralhome.com

GIBBS - Of E. Wareham and Rochester, August 21, 2004. Helen BH. Gibbs. Wife of the late Paul M. Gibbs. Mother of Johanna Cote and her husband, John, of Clarksville, MD and Paul D. Gibbs of Rochester and Wareham. Grandmother of Elizabeth Pricher, her husband Michael, of Columbus, OH and David J. Gibbs of Rochester. Great-grandmother of Olivia Kalin Pricher. Also survived by a sister-in-law, Winifred Blethen and her husband, Tyler, and sister-in-law, Kathryn Rounsville. Sister of the late John J. Balsavage and Anna M. Delsie. Funeral will be from the Stott, Chapman, Cole Gleason Funeral Home, 2599 Cranberry Highway (Rt. 28), Wareham, on Thursday, August 26th, at 9 A.M. followed by a Mass of Christian Burial at St. Patrick's Church, 82 High St., Wareham, at 10 A.M. Interment will be in Agawam Cemetery, Wareham. Visiting hours will be Wednesday, from 2-4 and 7-9 P.M.

HAMILTON - Helen C. "Nanny" (Gannon), 78 years old, died Monday, August 23, 2004, at the Metro West Medical Center in Framingham. She was the wife of the late Walter J. "Chick" Hamilton who died in 1989. Helen was born in Framingham, daughter of the late Thomas and Nellie (Kennedy) Garron. She was a lifelong resident and homemaker, and will be remembered for her many appearances at the Framingham Little League and softball games. Her grandchildren and great-grandchildren were the joy of her life. She was an avid Red Sox and Patriots fan and enjoyed collecting things of her Irish heritage. She is survived by two sons: John Hamilton and his good friend Charlotte Porreca of Medway, Norman Hamilton and his good friend Elaine Sylvester of Framingham, two daughters, Patricia Langle her husband Paul of Holliston, Marguerite Bedford and her husband Michael of Sandwich, one sister, Lillian Fannon of Bridgewater, two brothers, William Gannon and his wife Loretta of Yarmouth, Henry Gannon of Franklin nine grandchildren, Robert Langle wife Erika of Holliston, Michael Langley of Holliston, Michelle Bedford of Bourne, Michael and Molly Bedford, both of Sandwich, Ashley, Ryan, Devlin, and Jake Hamilton of Hopkinton, two great-grandchildren, Jason Mestieri of Bourne and Cassie Langley of Holliston. The funeral Mass will be held Thursday at 10 a.m. in St. Stephen's Church, 251 Concord St., Framingham. Burial will be in St. Stephen's Cemetery, Framingham. Calling hours at the Eugene J. McCarth Sons Funeral Home, 11 Lincoln St., Framingham, are on Wednesday, August 25, from 5-8 P.M.

HANLEY - Of Stratham, NH, formerly of Harwich and Billerica, August 21, 2004, by accident, Linda F. (Yurko) Hanley, wife of the late Robert W. Hanley. Funeral Thursday, from the SWEENEY MEMORIAL FUNERAL HOME, 66 Concord Rd., Billerica at 9:30 a.m. A Graveside Service will be held at the Fox Hill Cemetery, Billerica at 10:30 a.m. Relatives and friends respectfully invited. Visiting hours Wednesday, from 4-8 p.m. Funeral Director W. J. Laurendeau.

LOBBAN - Audrey P. (Palmer), of Falmouth, formerly of Milton and Weymouth, August 21, 2004. Beloved wife of the late John F. Lobban loving mother of Ruth Aldrich of Pocasset, John D. Lobban of Ft. Worth, TX, Robert P. Lobban of CT, and Gordon P. Lobban of Allen, TX sister of Sarah Palmer of TX, the late George Palmer and the late Charles Palmer. She is also survived by six grandchildren and four great-grandchildren. Visitation from 6-7 p.m. on Tuesday, August 24th, in Falmouth Baptist Church, 60 Central Park Ave., FALMOUTH and from 11-12 noon, on Wednesday, in Chapman, Cole Gleason Funeral Home, 5 Canton Ave., MILTON. A funeral service will begin at noon at the funeral home. Burial will follow in Milton Cemetery. For on-line guest book and directions, www.ccgfuneralhome.com

MCCABE - Thomas J., of Hyannis, formerly of Centerville and East Orange, NJ, August 21. Husband of Stella McCabe (Reilly) for 62 years father of Judith McCabe of Manasquan, NJ and the late Thomas T. McCabe who died in 1999 brother of Bernard McCabe of Allendale, NJ grandfather of Thomas S. McCabe of Kirkland, WA and Micahel D. McCabe of Sammanish, WA great grandfather of Michael G. McCabe. A Funeral Mass will be celebrated in Our Lady of Victory Church, 230 South Main Street, Centerville on Wednesday, Aguust 25, at 10 AM. Visiting Hours in the John-Lawrence Funeral Home, 3778 Falmouth Road (Route 28), Marstons Mills, on Tuesday, 5-8 PM. Burial in Mosswood Cemetery, Cotuit.

SIKORA - Walter L. of Pocasset, August 22 beloved husband of Violet M (Sobczyk) Sikora father of Robert Sikora of Tucson, AZ and Ronald Sikora of Cotuit. Brother of Stanley Sikora of Clifton, NJ and the late Joseph Sikora. He also leaves several nieces and nephews. A Funeral Service will be at 11:30 AM on Thursday, August 26, in the Chapman, Cole Gleason Funeral Home, 584 West Falmouth Highway (Route 28A), West Falmouth. Burial will follow in the V.A. National Cemetery of Massachusetts in Bourne. Visiting Hours will be Wednesday, from 5-8 PM. Memorial donations may be made to the Bourne Conservation Trust P.O. Box 203 Cataumet, MA 02534. For online obituary, directions and guestbook www.ccgfuneralhome.com.
